SRIMCA (Shri Ram Institute of Management and Computer Applications) - College Information

ABOUT SRIMCA
SRIMCA is a premier educational institution offering undergraduate and postgraduate programs in Computer Applications and Management Studies. The college is committed to providing quality education with a focus on holistic development.

COURSES OFFERED
- BCA (Bachelor of Computer Applications) - 3 years
- MCA (Master of Computer Applications) - 2 years
- BBA (Bachelor of Business Administration) - 3 years
- MBA (Master of Business Administration) - 2 years
- BSc IT (Information Technology) - 3 years

ADMISSION PROCEDURE
- For Undergraduate courses: Merit-based selection through entrance test
- For Postgraduate courses: Valid graduation score + GD/PI
- Application forms available on college website during admission season
- Last date for submission: As notified on website

FEES STRUCTURE
- BCA: Rs. 50,000 per year
- MCA: Rs. 60,000 per year
- BBA: Rs. 45,000 per year
- MBA: Rs. 80,000 per year
- Examination fees: As per university rules

EXAMINATION RULES
- Internal exams conducted monthly
- Mid-term exams at the end of first semester
- Final exams at the end of each semester
- Minimum passing marks: 35% (internal) and 40% (theory)
- Re-evaluation: Apply within 15 days of result declaration

ATTENDANCE POLICY
- Minimum 75% attendance mandatory for all students
- Medical leave: Submit medical certificate within 3 days
- Students with less than 75% attendance will not be eligible for exams

HOSTEL FACILITIES
- Separate hostels for boys and girls
